## $pK_a$ and $pK_b$
### Why?
Similarly to how $pH$ takes very large values and converts them to more manageable and understandable numbers, $pK_a$ does the same for $K_a$ and $K_b$

### Trends
$pK_a$ and $pK_b$ for an acid and conjugate base, or vise versa, will always add up to $14$ 
i.e.) for original and conjugate: $(pK_a)_{original} + (pK_b)_{conjugate} = 14$
